qas.question: The Porfiriato ended in which year?
The beginning of what ended the Porfiriato?
Who stated that Mexico was ready for a Democracy and that he would step down?
Who was incarcerated while running against Diaz?
Who took up arms in support of Madero?

context: The end of the Porfiriato came in <a0_0>1910<a0_0/> with the beginning of the <a1_0>Mexican Revolution<a1_0/>. <a2_0>Díaz<a2_0/> had stated that Mexico was ready for democracy and he would step down to allow other candidates to compete for the presidency, but Díaz decided to run again in 1910 for the last time against Francisco I. <a3_0>Madero<a3_0/>. During the campaign Díaz incarcerated Madero on election day in 1910. Díaz was announced the winner of the election by a landslide, triggering the revolution. Madero supporter <a4_0>Toribio Ortega<a4_0/> took up arms with a group of followers at Cuchillo Parado, Chihuahua on November 10, 1910.
